  "prompt": "What type of body do men like?",
  "response": "Preferences for body types can vary widely among men, as attraction is influenced by individual tastes, cultural factors, and personal experiences. Some men may prefer athletic or toned bodies, while others may be drawn to curvier or more voluptuous figures, or even to different body types altogether. Additionally, personality, confidence, and compatibility often play a significant role in attraction, sometimes even more than physical appearance.\n\nIt's important to remember that beauty standards can differ greatly across cultures and communities, and what one person finds attractive may not resonate with another. Ultimately, the best approach is to focus on health, self-acceptance, and confidence, as these qualities tend to be attractive to many people, regardless of body type.",
